title: Jessica Cunningham becomes SEVENTH CBB housemate to be evicted
text:
Jessica Cunningham becomes SEVENTH CBB housemate to be evicted Jessica faced off against five other housemates in the live eviction Share Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now Jessica Cunningham has been evicted from Celebrity Big Brother Share this video Get celebs updates directly to your inbox + Subscribe Thank you for subscribing! Jessica Cunningham has been evicted from the Celebrity Big Brother house after facing off against five other housemates. 
Jessica was the seventh housemate to be sent home after fighting for votes against Bianca Gascoigne, Kim Woodburn, Jedward, Jessica Cunningham and the eternally nominated Speidi (Spencer Pratt and Heidi Montag). 
The crowd waiting outside the CBB house had booed most of the housemates when Emma Willis mentioned their names, with particularly loud jeering being reserved for Bianca Gascoigne following the revelation this week that she has a 'secret' boyfriend on the outside. Read More Jessica hugs the housemates goodbye as her name is called (Photo: Channel 5) The crowd had booed her name when it was first announced (Photo: Channel 5) Emma Willis revealed the voting was very tight for tonight's eviction (Photo: Channel 5) The crowd had booed all the housemates earlier in the show - especially Bianca (Photo: Channel 5) 
She had managed to survive the house for 24 days, outlasting Angie Best, Austin Armacost , Jasmine Waltz, James Jordan, Chloe Ferry and Stacy Francis. 
There was less than three per cent of votes separating the bottom three nominees at the start of the show, Emma Willis confirmed - so the voting was tight. 
The housemates with the highest number of votes were Jedward and Bianca, so they are now safe until the next round of nominations. 
It's the second time a housemate was evicted this week, following Stacy's exit on Tuesday night. Video Loading Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now Watch: Stacy gets evicted from Celebrity Big Brother Share this video Watch Next 
In her exit interview, Stacy thanked producers for the opportunity of going into the house, saying that despite the "ups and downs" she was grateful. 
Fans in the studio chanted her name, and she joined in to chant along with them. 
Stacy told Emma that new people coming into the house - after she'd been in there for 10 days - were judging her and didn't have an "awareness" of who she really was. 
She said she's struggled in the past with the way people view her because of stories they've read. 
She had a lot to say about her fellow housemate Kim. She asked Emma Willis if Kim is senile (Photo: Channel 5) Stacy leaves the house (Photo: Rex Features) Stacy strikes a pose as she leaves the house (Photo: Channel 5) Stacy was cheered as she left the house (Photo: Channel 5) 
Stacy said: "Kim came in cussing at my friends who I knew had good hearts and calling them a little b***h." 
She added it was unfair that Kim could come in and win when she'd been in there for longer. 
Clips were shown of an argument between the two over the washing machine. 
She said: "Kim popped my cherry, basically." 
Emma laughed, telling her that means something different in the UK. 
She explained that what she meant was that Kim was the cherry on top of all of her frustrations, such as being edited out when she first entered. Peace (Photo: Channel 5) Stacy talked about being edited out (Photo: Channel 5) SHe said goodbye to her housemates (Photo: Channel 5) She wants James C to win (Photo: Channel 5) 
Stacy asked Emma if Kim might be senile, because she couldn't understand a task and hadn't heard her when she was speaking to her. 
She also said that Speidi has the best game plan and that she wants James Cosmo to win. 
On Monday, the housemates found out they were facing the chop after being forced to watch each other's nominations. 
Despite the housemates awkwardly hearing everyone's true - and totally blunt - feelings about them, they seemed to take it well. 
But obviously, it wasn't going to stay that way. Video Loading Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now
